# ============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Backend Architecture (DRAAD 202)
# ============================================================================
#
# The backend /api/roster/solve route now:
# 1. Accepts POST with { roster_id }
# 2. Collects roster data from Supabase
# 3. Sends to GREEDY_ENDPOINT (single attempt, 30s timeout)
# 4. Processes response with DRAAD155 UPDATE pattern
# 5. Returns success with coverage % and assignments
#
# NO RETRY LOGIC - Single attempt per DRAAD 202 requirement
# Error messages are in Dutch for user-friendly feedback
#
# Expected GREEDY Response:
# {
#   "status": "SUCCESS" | "PARTIAL" | "FAILED",
#   "coverage": 95.5,
#   "assignments": [...],
#   "total_assignments": 150,
#   "solve_time_seconds": 2.5
# }
#
# Expected solverruns database update:
# - status: SUCCESS/PARTIAL/FAILED
# - coveragerate: 95.5
# - totalassignments: 150
# - solvetimeseconds: 2.5
# - source: "greedy" (NOT "ortsolve")
#

